SCORING RUBRIC (total: 100 points):

## 1. Technical Skills & Stack Breadth (25 points)
Score based on the range and relevance of technical skills mentioned.
- Languages, frameworks, tools, databases, platforms
- Academic or personal exposure counts
- Bonus for Singapore-relevant stacks (cloud, data, enterprise, web)

Scoring guide:
- 20-25: Strong multi-stack evidence with relevant tools (e.g. React, Flask, SQL, Python, Excel automation)
- 13-19: Solid skills list with some demonstrated use in projects or work
- 6-12: Basic skills mentioned but little evidence of application
- 0-5: Minimal or no technical skills visible

## 2. Projects & Delivery (35 points)
Score based on technical projects — university assignments, FYPs, personal projects, hackathons, internship deliverables.
- Academic group projects count fully
- Coursework projects count if they show real technical work
- GitHub links are a bonus but NOT required
- Deployed/live projects are a bonus but NOT required
- What matters: complexity, tech stack used, your individual contribution, what was built

Scoring guide:
- 28-35: 2+ substantial projects with clear stack, architecture, individual contribution, and outcomes
- 18-27: 1-2 projects with decent technical depth and described implementation
- 8-17: Projects mentioned but light on technical detail
- 0-7: No meaningful project evidence

## 3. Applied / Work Experience (25 points)
Score based on any work experience where technical or analytical skills were applied.
- Internships, part-time roles, NS, admin roles with automation/analytics all count
- Excel VBA, data reporting, system use, automation = valid technical signals
- Even non-tech roles count if they show analytical thinking, process improvement, or tool use

Scoring guide:
- 20-25: Clear technical or analytical contribution in at least one role (e.g. automation, data work, systems)
- 13-19: Some tech-adjacent work (e.g. Excel reporting, social media analytics, content tools)
- 6-12: Mostly non-technical but shows transferable skills
- 0-5: No work experience or purely manual roles with no transferable signals

## 4. Professional Readiness & Presentation (15 points)
Score based on how job-ready the candidate appears overall.
- Clear structure, quantified achievements, action verbs
- LinkedIn or contact info present
- Leadership, teamwork, communication evidence
- Studying a relevant degree (e.g. Computer Science, IT, Engineering, Data)

Scoring guide:
- 12-15: Polished, well-structured, quantified, relevant degree, professional links
- 8-11: Mostly clear with some gaps in quantification or structure
- 4-7: Decent but hard to scan, missing key details
- 0-3: Poor structure, missing information, hard to assess

---

BONUS POINTS (max +10):
- +3: GitHub profile or repo links present (even if not verified)
- +3: Any deployed or live project mentioned (URL, platform, hosting)
- +2: Relevant certifications (AWS, Google, Microsoft, cybersecurity, etc.)
- +2: Leadership role in a tech/computing club or organisation

DEDUCTIONS (max -10):
- -3: Significant formatting issues or walls of unstructured text
- -3: Skills listed with zero evidence of ever using them
- -2: Dates missing or inconsistent across experience entries

